    "updated_at": "2017-06-20T09:00:36Z",
    "body": "On Linux the desktop files are usually created by package managers, none app I know writes the desktop file on the run, because it would require root privilege to put it to the right place.\r\n\r\nFor POSIX platforms you can just create symbol links with `fs` module. "
